B.Td=new A.d0("Led with a feature carousel before the first form screen","Both the competitive analysis and the sessions pointed at the same gap \u2014 people had no idea what Perro would do for them before being asked to hand over information.","Tested against a minimal version without it. The carousel did better on engagement and downstream completion, and became the production baseline.",B.bd)
B.Tf=new A.d0("Replaced mandatory photo upload with an avatar system and optional image","Sessions showed this was a silent exit trigger. People left to find a suitable photo and frequently didn\u2019t come back, so making it optional removed a low-value blocker.","Drop-off at the dog profile step fell noticeably after launch, and people could finish setup in one sitting without leaving the app.",B.bd)
B.Tn=new A.d0("Added a plain-language permissions explainer before the OS prompts","Abrupt system dialogs for location and notifications appeared out of nowhere. Most people either dismissed them or felt ambushed.","Acceptance improved. People who read the explainer were far more likely to grant both location and notification access.",B.bd)
